REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: COMMERCIAL SCREEN INDEX 44 (0.1 M HEPES  
REMARK 280 PH 7.5, 25% W/V PEG3350) WAS CHOSEN FOR SARS-COV-2 NSP1 (RESIDUES    
REMARK 280 10 TO 126) CRYSTALLISATION IN LARGE QUANTITIES USING HANGING DROP    
REMARK 280 METHOD. FROZEN STOCKS OF SARS-COV-2 NSP1 (RESIDUES 10 TO 126)        
REMARK 280 WERE THAWED ON ICE AND CENTRIFUGED IN A THERMO SCIENTIFIC PICO       
REMARK 280 17 MICROCENTRIFUGE, 24-PL ROTOR AT 4 DEGREES, 20000 RPM FOR 10       
REMARK 280 MIN TO REMOVE AGGREGATES BEFORE THE DETERMINATION OF THE PROTEIN     
REMARK 280 CONCENTRATION. SUBSEQUENTLY, THE PROTEIN STOCK WAS DILUTED TO        
REMARK 280 20 MG/ ML WITH PRECRYSTALLISATION BUFFER (10 MM HEPES AND 300 MM     
REMARK 280 NACL). 400 UL OF INDEX CONDITION 44 WAS ADDED INTO EACH RESERVOIR    
REMARK 280 WELL. FIVE PROTEIN DROPS WERE SET ON EACH COVER SLIP BY MIXING 1 UL  
REMARK 280 OF PROTEIN SOLUTION WITH 1 UL OF THE RESERVOIR. THE 24-WELL LINBRO   
REMARK 280 PLATES WERE INCUBATED AT 18 DEGREES., VAPOR DIFFUSION, HANGING       
REMARK 280 DROP, TEMPERATURE 291.15K, PH 7.5                                    
